                      &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=221807&TOPIC_ID=22931&FORUM_ID=13"><img src="images/icon_reply_topic.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="Reply with Quote" title="Reply with Quote" align="absmiddle" hspace="6" /></a>
                      <hr noshade size="2"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> When you run out of mana, you can run to the zoneline. When you run out of hit points, you can't. <br /><br />Try to balance HP/int/mana/whatnot to allow you to cast 6-8 "level appropriate" spells per full bar of mana. Not your pet, 'cause pets are HUGE mana compared to other stuff. Go with, like, your latest tap or DOT. Head to a newbie area, target snake/rat/bat, tap, target a new one, tap again. If you can tap 6-8 before you're OOM, you're fine for mana. Then start working on HP.<br /><br />It's all a big juggling act as to what's "best" for you. If you're in a group all the time, getting ID (improved damage) focus might be better than BA (burning affliction). If you solo, the reverse might be true. <br /><br />Does that make sense?</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
