                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Before PoP, HP &gt;&gt;&gt; Mana. Even if your manapool is small, we're the best at regening mana (with our hps) We're less depend on our manapool size than any other casters (except shaman, but they also advocate that HP/AC &gt; wis)<br /><br />When you hit PoP tiers 2+, HP become less of a concern. +1K hp don't make much difference when the mobs quad for 500+. And with ToM/SK, you will never have problem again with lich.<br /><br />Now with LdoN, Int is even less a problem. Just add int augment at your HP/Mana gear.<br /><br />Anyway, it depends on you. Do you have problem with lich ? Get more HP until you feel comfortable. You end your fight OOM at 90% HP ? Go for mana item (or Int if &lt; 200)<br />And as Taroo said " When you run out of mana, you can run to the zoneline. When you run out of hit points, you can't"<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
